vatar/discourse.urho3d.io/1vank/{size}/768_2.png","created_at":"2015-08-02T20:36:08.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eAnother question. It is possible in Urho mix (blending) two materials? Like \u003ca href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OlxfJlNK1RM\"\u003eyoutube.com/watch?v=OlxfJlNK1RM\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:06:13.437Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":65,"readers_count":64,"score":28.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":1230,"topic_slug":"glass-material","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OlxfJlNK1RM","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"OGRE - \"layered blending\" sample - YouTube","clicks":21}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":true,"admin":false,"staff":true,"user_id":263,"hidden":false,"trust_level":4,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":6995,"name":"","username":"boberfly","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/b/aeb1de/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-08-03T00:15:33.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHi,\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSure but you need to source refraction from somewhere:\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/bin/CoreData/RenderPaths/Forward.xml\" data-bbcode=\"true\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttps://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/bin/CoreData/RenderPaths/Forward.xml\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nPretty sure the water shader grabs the environment texture unit from this pass.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/bin/CoreData/Techniques/Water.xml\" data-bbcode=\"true\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttps://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/bin/CoreData/Techniques/Water.xml\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/bin/CoreData/Shaders/GLSL/Water.glsl\" data-bbcode=\"true\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttps://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/bin/CoreData/Shaders/GLSL/Water.glsl\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nYep. But I think it‚Äôs an inverted camera matrix maybe, so it‚Äôs only good for perfectly flat horizontal water. You might need to re-jig the renderpath to just source the whole framebuffer result into a texture and then distort it with the normals of the sphere, yay refraction.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFor reflection you‚Äôll need some cube map, maybe bound to the zone‚Äôs texture unit slot.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:06:13.499Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":5,"reads":64,"readers_count":63,"score":37.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":1230,"topic_slug":"glass-material","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/bin/CoreData/Techniques/Water.xml","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Urho3D/Water.xml at master ¬∑ urho3d/Urho3D ¬∑ GitHub","clicks":8},{"url":"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/bin/CoreData/Shaders/GLSL/Water.glsl","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Urho3D/Water.glsl at master ¬∑ urho3d/Urho3D ¬∑ GitHub","clicks":8},{"url":"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/bin/CoreData/RenderPaths/Forward.xml","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Urho3D/Forward.xml at master ¬∑ urho3d/Urho3D ¬∑ GitHub","clicks":6}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":69,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":7005,"name":"","username":"1vanK","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/1vank/{size}/768_2.png","created_at":"2015-08-03T08:35:17.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI combined water and specular and receive interesting result\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGlassTechnique.xml\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e\u0026lt;technique vs=\"Water\" ps=\"Water\" \u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;pass name=\"refract\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;pass name=\"litalpha\" depthwrite=\"false\" blend=\"addalpha\" vs=\"LitSolid\" ps=\"LitSolid\" vsdefines=\"NOUV\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/technique\u0026gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGlass.xml\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e\u0026lt;?xml version=\"1.0\"?\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;material\u0026gt;\n\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"NoiseSpeed\" value=\"0 0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"NoiseTiling\" value=\"50\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"NoiseStrength\" value=\"0.02\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"FresnelPower\" value=\"5\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"WaterTint\" value=\"1 1 1\" /\u0026gt;\n\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"MatDiffColor\" value=\"0.12 0.12 0.12 1\"/\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"MatSpecColor\" value=\"1 1 1 300\"/\u0026gt;\n\n    \u0026lt;technique name=\"Techniques/GlassTechnique.xml\"/\u0026gt;\n\n\u0026lt;/material\u0026gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"http://s019.radikal.ru/i640/1508/91/079df0dff77c.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"597\" height=\"350\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBut there is a strange bug: when near on front scene is object with water